The paper deals with a problem of maximizing the weight of a chosen subset of elements under certain packing constraints, which is a classic problem in computer science. The use of stochastic probing and the consideration of matroid and knapsack constraints suggest that the paper may belong to the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
